eu.brengard.businesscalendar.entitites

Class BusinessTimeSlot

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.brengard.businesscalendar.entitites.BusinessTimeSlot
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class BusinessTimeSlot
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A time slot, defined by a start time and an end time.

    This class provides methods to create and handle a time slot. This includes a method to get the Duration getDuration two LocalTimes by counting only the time inside the time slot.

    A time slot is constituted of two LocalTimes :

    • A start time, inclusive.
    • An end time, exclusive.
    Since:
    1.8
    Author:
    Nicolas BRENGARD (eu.brengard.businesscalendar.entitites@brengard.eu)
    See Also:
    java.time, Serialized Form
